<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910319-0116</DOCNO><DOCID>910319-0116.</DOCID><HL>   Technology Brief -- WordStar International Inc.:   Company Enters Agreement   To Buy Lifetree Software</HL><DATE>02/25/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   WDST</CO><IN>SOFTWARE (SOF)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   WordStar International Inc. said it agreed to acquireLifetree Software, developer of Correct Grammar, agrammar-checking application for personal computers. Termsweren't disclosed.   The acquisition will give the Novato, Calif., companyimmediate market share in the fast-growing writing toolssegment for computer software, WordStar said.</LP><TEXT>   Lifetree, based in Sausalito, will become WordStar'sWriting Tools Division; Camilo Wilson, founder and chiefexecutive officer of Lifetree, will be the division's vicepresident.</TEXT></DOC>